{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013EcpDM1FXXtUZcSzx75wgk","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t//! Power-cut + OS-crash durability harnesses (AC-034a / AC-034b / AC-034c).\n2\t//!\n3\t//! Both bodies are gated on `AGENT_LONG=1` per `tests/perf_gates.rs`\n4\t//! precedent: `agent-verify` skips the long run, the dedicated soak\n5\t//! pipeline opts in. The harness is NOT a soak (open-ended) — it runs\n6\t//! `P-PWR-TRIALS = 100` (AC-034a/b) or `P-OS-TRIALS = 50` (AC-034c)\n7\t//! deterministic trials and asserts the bounds in `dev/acceptance.md`.\n8\t//!\n9\t//! Substrate notes:\n10\t//!   - Power-cut victim is the test binary itself, re-entered through\n11\t//!     `Command::new(current_exe())` with an env-var sentinel that\n12\t//!     routes execution to `_power_cut_victim_entry` (test-binary-as-\n13\t//!     victim trick). No dedicated `cargo-bin` victim is required.\n14\t//!   - OS-crash (AC-034c) requires a VM image + sysrq trigger per\n15\t//!     `dev/acceptance.md` § AC-034c fixture; that substrate does not\n16\t//!     exist in this repo, so the AC-034c body surfaces as a runtime\n17\t//!     blocker and the trial loop returns early. See\n18\t//!     `dev/plans/runs/12-D-durability-harnesses-output.json`.\n19\t\n20\tuse std::path::PathBuf;\n21\tuse std::process::{Command, Stdio};\n22\tuse std::time::{Duration, Instant, SystemTime, UNIX_EPOCH};\n23\t\n24\tuse fathomdb_engine::{Engine, PreparedWrite};\n25\tuse tempfile::TempDir;\n26\t\n27\tfn long_run_enabled() -> bool {\n28\t    std::env::var_os(\"AGENT_LONG\").is_some()\n29\t}\n30\t\n31\tconst P_PWR_TRIALS: usize = 100;\n32\tconst AC_034B_P99_BUDGET_MS: u128 = 100;\n33\t// Per-trial wait between victim startup and SIGKILL. Drawn uniformly\n34\t// from [PWR_MIN_KILL_MS, PWR_MAX_KILL_MS) so kills land at varied\n35\t// commit-cycle phases per AC-034a/b fixture spec.\n36\tconst PWR_MIN_KILL_MS: u64 = 30;\n37\tconst PWR_MAX_KILL_MS: u64 = 180;\n38\t// Time budget for the victim child to die after SIGKILL before we\n39\t// declare the trial degenerate. Generous; SIGKILL is immediate.\n40\tconst VICTIM_REAP_BUDGET: Duration = Duration::from_secs(5);\n41\t\n42\t// ── Victim entry-point ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n43\t\n44\t/// Test-binary-as-victim entry. Re-invoked from\n45\t/// `Command::new(current_exe()) --exact --ignored _power_cut_victim_entry`\n46\t/// with `FATHOMDB_POWER_CUT_VICTIM_DB` set. Without the env var the test\n47\t/// is a no-op so plain `cargo test --test durability_soak -- --ignored`\n48\t/// (no env var) is still safe.\n49\t#[test]\n50\t#[ignore = \"test-binary-as-victim entry-point for the AC-034a/b power-cut harness\"]\n51\tfn _power_cut_victim_entry() {\n52\t    let Some(db_path_os) = std::env::var_os(\"FATHOMDB_POWER_CUT_VICTIM_DB\") else {\n53\t        return;\n54\t    };\n55\t    let path = PathBuf::from(db_path_os);\n56\t    let opened = Engine::open(&path).expect(\"victim engine open\");\n57\t    // Commit single-row writes carrying the wall-clock timestamp of the\n58\t    // commit in the body field. The parent recovers the maximum body\n59\t    // value after kill — that is the last-surviving-commit timestamp\n60\t    // per AC-034b measurement protocol.\n61\t    loop {\n62\t        let body = micros_since_epoch().to_string();\n63\t        opened\n64\t            .engine\n65\t            .write(&[PreparedWrite::Node { kind: \"doc\".to_string(), body, source_id: None }])\n66\t            .expect(\"victim write\");\n67\t    }\n68\t}\n69\t\n70\tfn micros_since_epoch() -> u128 {\n71\t    SystemTime::now().duration_since(UNIX_EPOCH).expect(\"clock\").as_micros()\n72\t}\n73\t\n74\t// ── AC-034a + AC-034b: power-cut harness ────────────────────────────────────\n75\t\n76\t#[test]\n77\tfn ac_034a_and_b_power_cut_zero_corruption_and_p99_lost_commit() {\n78\t    if !long_run_enabled() {\n79\t        eprintln!(\"AC-034a/b skipped (AGENT_LONG not set)\");\n80\t        return;\n81\t    }\n82\t    let outcomes = run_power_cut_trials(P_PWR_TRIALS);\n83\t\n84\t    // AC-034a: integrity_check == \"ok\" on every trial.\n85\t    let bad: Vec<_> = outcomes.iter().filter(|o| o.integrity != \"ok\").collect();\n86\t    assert!(\n87\t        bad.is_empty(),\n88\t        \"AC-034a: {} of {} trials returned non-ok integrity_check: {:?}\",\n89\t        bad.len(),\n90\t        outcomes.len(),\n91\t        bad,\n92\t    );\n93\t\n94\t    // AC-034b: p99 lost-commit duration ≤ 100 ms.\n95\t    let mut lost: Vec<u128> = outcomes.iter().filter_map(|o| o.lost_commit_ms).collect();\n96\t    assert!(\n97\t        lost.len() >= (outcomes.len() * 9 / 10),\n98\t        \"AC-034b: only {} of {} trials yielded a surviving commit; \\\n99\t         the harness is killing the victim before any write lands\",\n100\t        lost.len(),\n101\t        outcomes.len(),\n102\t    );\n103\t    lost.sort_unstable();\n104\t    let p99_index = ((lost.len() as f64 * 0.99).ceil() as usize).saturating_sub(1);\n105\t    let p99 = lost[p99_index];\n106\t    eprintln!(\"AC-034a: integrity_check ok on {}/{} trials\", outcomes.len(), outcomes.len());\n107\t    eprintln!(\n108\t        \"AC-034b: lost-commit ms — n={}, min={}, median={}, p99={}\",\n109\t        lost.len(),\n110\t        lost[0],\n111\t        lost[lost.len() / 2],\n112\t        p99,\n113\t    );\n114\t    assert!(\n115\t        p99 <= AC_034B_P99_BUDGET_MS,\n116\t        \"AC-034b: lost-commit p99 = {} ms > {} ms budget\",\n117\t        p99,\n118\t        AC_034B_P99_BUDGET_MS,\n119\t    );\n120\t}\n121\t\n122\t#[derive(Debug)]\n123\tstruct TrialOutcome {\n124\t    integrity: String,\n125\t    lost_commit_ms: Option<u128>,\n126\t}\n127\t\n128\tfn run_power_cut_trials(trials: usize) -> Vec<TrialOutcome> {\n129\t    let exe = std::env::current_exe().expect(\"current_exe\");\n130\t    let mut outcomes = Vec::with_capacity(trials);\n131\t    for trial in 0..trials {\n132\t        let dir = TempDir::new().expect(\"tempdir\");\n133\t        let db_path = dir.path().join(\"power-cut.sqlite\");\n134\t\n135\t        let mut child = Command::new(&exe)\n136\t            .args([\"--exact\", \"--ignored\", \"_power_cut_victim_entry\"])\n137\t            .env(\"FATHOMDB_POWER_CUT_VICTIM_DB\", &db_path)\n138\t            // Per-trial stdio drop; the parent does not parse victim\n139\t            // output, and leaving stdout connected to the parent test\n140\t            // would interleave with `cargo test` framing.\n141\t            .stdout(Stdio::null())\n142\t            .stderr(Stdio::null())\n143\t            .spawn()\n144\t            .expect(\"spawn victim\");\n145\t        let pid = child.id() as i32;\n146\t\n147\t        // Allow the child to start writing before we kill it. Without\n148\t        // a floor, the kill races the engine-open path and most trials\n149\t        // produce zero surviving commits.\n150\t        let sleep_ms = trial_sleep_ms(trial);\n151\t        std::thread::sleep(Duration::from_millis(sleep_ms));\n152\t\n153\t        let kill_micros = micros_since_epoch();\n154\t        // SAFETY: `pid` is owned by `child` and we have not yet\n155\t        // wait()-ed for it. SIGKILL on a still-running PID is defined.\n156\t        let kill_rc = unsafe { libc::kill(pid, libc::SIGKILL) };\n157\t        if kill_rc != 0 {\n158\t            panic!(\"trial {trial}: SIGKILL failed: {}\", std::io::Error::last_os_error());\n159\t        }\n160\t\n161\t        // Reap the child. SIGKILL is immediate, but `wait` is the only\n162\t        // way to release the zombie + confirm the process is gone\n163\t        // before we touch the WAL file from the parent.\n164\t        wait_with_budget(&mut child, VICTIM_REAP_BUDGET, trial);\n165\t\n166\t        let last_commit_micros = read_last_commit_micros(&db_path);\n167\t        let integrity = run_integrity_check(&db_path);\n168\t        let lost_commit_ms = last_commit_micros.map(|last| {\n169\t            // `kill_micros >= last` holds by construction (last is read\n170\t            // from a committed row, kill_micros samples after spawn).\n171\t            // Saturating sub guards against clock jumps under load.\n172\t            kill_micros.saturating_sub(last) / 1_000\n173\t        });\n174\t        outcomes.push(TrialOutcome { integrity, lost_commit_ms });\n175\t    }\n176\t    outcomes\n177\t}\n178\t\n179\tfn trial_sleep_ms(trial: usize) -> u64 {\n180\t    // Deterministic linear-congruential sequence keyed off the trial\n181\t    // index; trials remain reproducible across runs while still\n182\t    // sweeping the kill point across the commit cycle.\n183\t    let mixed = (trial as u64)\n184\t        .wrapping_mul(6_364_136_223_846_793_005)\n185\t        .wrapping_add(1_442_695_040_888_963_407);\n186\t    let range = PWR_MAX_KILL_MS - PWR_MIN_KILL_MS;\n187\t    PWR_MIN_KILL_MS + (mixed % range)\n188\t}\n189\t\n190\tfn wait_with_budget(child: &mut std::process::Child, budget: Duration, trial: usize) {\n191\t    let started = Instant::now();\n192\t    loop {\n193\t        match child.try_wait() {\n194\t            Ok(Some(_)) => return,\n195\t            Ok(None) => {\n196\t                if started.elapsed() > budget {\n197\t                    panic!(\"trial {trial}: victim did not exit within {:?} after SIGKILL\", budget);\n198\t                }\n199\t                std::thread::sleep(Duration::from_millis(5));\n200\t            }\n201\t            Err(err) => panic!(\"trial {trial}: wait failed: {err}\"),\n202\t        }\n203\t    }\n204\t}\n205\t\n206\tfn read_last_commit_micros(db_path: &std::path::Path) -> Option<u128> {\n207\t    // Read via the engine to confirm the engine itself can recover the\n208\t    // killed database; raw rusqlite on a half-recovered DB might paper\n209\t    // over an open-path defect.\n210\t    let opened = Engine::open(db_path).expect(\"post-kill engine open\");\n211\t    let path = opened.engine.path().to_path_buf();\n212\t    opened.engine.close().expect(\"post-kill close\");\n213\t    drop(opened);\n214\t\n215\t    let conn = rusqlite::Connection::open(&path).expect(\"post-kill rusqlite open\");\n216\t    // Bodies are decimal microsecond timestamps; ordering by CAST keeps\n217\t    // semantics correct if the column is TEXT-affinity.\n218\t    let max: Option<String> = conn\n219\t        .query_row(\n220\t            \"SELECT body FROM canonical_nodes\n221\t              WHERE kind = 'doc'\n222\t              ORDER BY CAST(body AS INTEGER) DESC LIMIT 1\",\n223\t            [],\n224\t            |row| row.get(0),\n225\t        )\n226\t        .ok();\n227\t    max.and_then(|raw| raw.parse::<u128>().ok())\n228\t}\n229\t\n230\tfn run_integrity_check(db_path: &std::path::Path) -> String {\n231\t    let conn = rusqlite::Connection::open(db_path).expect(\"integrity rusqlite open\");\n232\t    conn.query_row(\"PRAGMA integrity_check\", [], |row| row.get::<_, String>(0))\n233\t        .unwrap_or_else(|err| format!(\"integrity_check query failed: {err}\"))\n234\t}\n235\t\n236\t// ── AC-034c: OS-crash harness ───────────────────────────────────────────────\n237\t\n238\t#[test]\n239\t#[ignore = \"AC-034c blocked on missing VM/sysrq fixture; see Phase 12-D \\\n240\t            output JSON (blocker-3). Do NOT clear the #[ignore] until \\\n241\t            the VM image lands in dev/test-plan.md.\"]\n242\tfn ac_034c_os_crash_zero_committed_tx_loss() {\n243\t    // Intentionally empty body. The `#[ignore]` carries the blocker so\n244\t    // `cargo test --release --test durability_soak ac_034c` reports\n245\t    // \"1 ignored\" — visible in CI logs, not a silent skip — without\n246\t    // pretending to verify the AC. Substituting `kill -9` for an OS\n247\t    // crash would be silent AC weakening (per\n248\t    // `feedback_reliability_principles.md` no-punt rule).\n249\t    //\n250\t    // To unblock: land the KVM image + `echo c > /proc/sysrq-trigger`\n251\t    // workflow per `dev/acceptance.md` § AC-034c fixture, clear the\n252\t    // `#[ignore]`, and wire trial loop here following the AC-034a/b\n253\t    // shape above.\n254\t}\n255\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3dcf3508-c16d-46fb-9860-076600a60569","uuid":"2b0e9def-2a48-48a7-9e26-f6c73fb158ba","timestamp":"2026-05-17T19:25:10.860Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-12-D-durability-harnesses-20260517T185755Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/durability_soak.rs","content":"//! Power-cut + OS-crash durability harnesses (AC-034a / AC-034b / AC-034c).\n//!\n//! Both bodies are gated on `AGENT_LONG=1` per `tests/perf_gates.rs`\n//! precedent: `agent-verify` skips the long run, the dedicated soak\n//! pipeline opts in. The harness is NOT a soak (open-ended) — it runs\n//! `P-PWR-TRIALS = 100` (AC-034a/b) or `P-OS-TRIALS = 50` (AC-034c)\n//! deterministic trials and asserts the bounds in `dev/acceptance.md`.\n//!\n//! Substrate notes:\n//!   - Power-cut victim is the test binary itself, re-entered through\n//!     `Command::new(current_exe())` with an env-var sentinel that\n//!     routes execution to `_power_cut_victim_entry` (test-binary-as-\n//!     victim trick). No dedicated `cargo-bin` victim is required.\n//!   - OS-crash (AC-034c) requires a VM image + sysrq trigger per\n//!     `dev/acceptance.md` § AC-034c fixture; that substrate does not\n//!     exist in this repo, so the AC-034c body surfaces as a runtime\n//!     blocker and the trial loop returns early. See\n//!     `dev/plans/runs/12-D-durability-harnesses-output.json`.\n\nuse std::path::PathBuf;\nuse std::process::{Command, Stdio};\nuse std::time::{Duration, Instant, SystemTime, UNIX_EPOCH};\n\nuse fathomdb_engine::{Engine, PreparedWrite};\nuse tempfile::TempDir;\n\nfn long_run_enabled() -> bool {\n    std::env::var_os(\"AGENT_LONG\").is_some()\n}\n\nconst P_PWR_TRIALS: usize = 100;\nconst AC_034B_P99_BUDGET_MS: u128 = 100;\n// Per-trial wait between victim startup and SIGKILL. Drawn uniformly\n// from [PWR_MIN_KILL_MS, PWR_MAX_KILL_MS) so kills land at varied\n// commit-cycle phases per AC-034a/b fixture spec.\nconst PWR_MIN_KILL_MS: u64 = 30;\nconst PWR_MAX_KILL_MS: u64 = 180;\n// Time budget for the victim child to die after SIGKILL before we\n// declare the trial degenerate. Generous; SIGKILL is immediate.\nconst VICTIM_REAP_BUDGET: Duration = Duration::from_secs(5);\n\n// ── Victim entry-point ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/// Test-binary-as-victim entry. Re-invoked from\n/// `Command::new(current_exe()) --exact --ignored _power_cut_victim_entry`\n/// with `FATHOMDB_POWER_CUT_VICTIM_DB` set. Without the env var the test\n/// is a no-op so plain `cargo test --test durability_soak -- --ignored`\n/// (no env var) is still safe.\n#[test]\n#[ignore = \"test-binary-as-victim entry-point for the AC-034a/b power-cut harness\"]\nfn _power_cut_victim_entry() {\n    let Some(db_path_os) = std::env::var_os(\"FATHOMDB_POWER_CUT_VICTIM_DB\") else {\n        return;\n    };\n    let path = PathBuf::from(db_path_os);\n    let opened = Engine::open(&path).expect(\"victim engine open\");\n    // Commit single-row writes carrying the wall-clock timestamp of the\n    // commit in the body field. The parent recovers the maximum body\n    // value after kill — that is the last-surviving-commit timestamp\n    // per AC-034b measurement protocol.\n    loop {\n        let body = micros_since_epoch().to_string();\n        opened\n            .engine\n            .write(&[PreparedWrite::Node { kind: \"doc\".to_string(), body, source_id: None }])\n            .expect(\"victim write\");\n    }\n}\n\nfn micros_since_epoch() -> u128 {\n    SystemTime::now().duration_since(UNIX_EPOCH).expect(\"clock\").as_micros()\n}\n\n// ── AC-034a + AC-034b: power-cut harness ────────────────────────────────────\n\n#[test]\nfn ac_034a_and_b_power_cut_zero_corruption_and_p99_lost_commit() {\n    if !long_run_enabled() {\n        eprintln!(\"AC-034a/b skipped (AGENT_LONG not set)\");\n        return;\n    }\n    let outcomes = run_power_cut_trials(P_PWR_TRIALS);\n\n    // AC-034a: integrity_check == \"ok\" on every trial.\n    let bad: Vec<_> = outcomes.iter().filter(|o| o.integrity != \"ok\").collect();\n    assert!(\n        bad.is_empty(),\n        \"AC-034a: {} of {} trials returned non-ok integrity_check: {:?}\",\n        bad.len(),\n        outcomes.len(),\n        bad,\n    );\n\n    // AC-034b: p99 lost-commit duration ≤ 100 ms.\n    let mut lost: Vec<u128> = outcomes.iter().filter_map(|o| o.lost_commit_ms).collect();\n    assert!(\n        lost.len() >= (outcomes.len() * 9 / 10),\n        \"AC-034b: only {} of {} trials yielded a surviving commit; \\\n         the harness is killing the victim before any write lands\",\n        lost.len(),\n        outcomes.len(),\n    );\n    lost.sort_unstable();\n    let p99_index = ((lost.len() as f64 * 0.99).ceil() as usize).saturating_sub(1);\n    let p99 = lost[p99_index];\n    eprintln!(\"AC-034a: integrity_check ok on {}/{} trials\", outcomes.len(), outcomes.len());\n    eprintln!(\n        \"AC-034b: lost-commit ms — n={}, min={}, median={}, p99={}\",\n        lost.len(),\n        lost[0],\n        lost[lost.len() / 2],\n        p99,\n    );\n    assert!(\n        p99 <= AC_034B_P99_BUDGET_MS,\n        \"AC-034b: lost-commit p99 = {} ms > {} ms budget\",\n        p99,\n        AC_034B_P99_BUDGET_MS,\n    );\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug)]\nstruct TrialOutcome {\n    integrity: String,\n    lost_commit_ms: Option<u128>,\n}\n\nfn run_power_cut_trials(trials: usize) -> Vec<TrialOutcome> {\n    let exe = std::env::current_exe().expect(\"current_exe\");\n    let mut outcomes = Vec::with_capacity(trials);\n    for trial in 0..trials {\n        let dir = TempDir::new().expect(\"tempdir\");\n        let db_path = dir.path().join(\"power-cut.sqlite\");\n\n        let mut child = Command::new(&exe)\n            .args([\"--exact\", \"--ignored\", \"_power_cut_victim_entry\"])\n            .env(\"FATHOMDB_POWER_CUT_VICTIM_DB\", &db_path)\n            // Per-trial stdio drop; the parent does not parse victim\n            // output, and leaving stdout connected to the parent test\n            // would interleave with `cargo test` framing.\n            .stdout(Stdio::null())\n            .stderr(Stdio::null())\n            .spawn()\n            .expect(\"spawn victim\");\n        let pid = child.id() as i32;\n\n        // Allow the child to start writing before we kill it. Without\n        // a floor, the kill races the engine-open path and most trials\n        // produce zero surviving commits.\n        let sleep_ms = trial_sleep_ms(trial);\n        std::thread::sleep(Duration::from_millis(sleep_ms));\n\n        let kill_micros = micros_since_epoch();\n        // SAFETY: `pid` is owned by `child` and we have not yet\n        // wait()-ed for it. SIGKILL on a still-running PID is defined.\n        let kill_rc = unsafe { libc::kill(pid, libc::SIGKILL) };\n        if kill_rc != 0 {\n            panic!(\"trial {trial}: SIGKILL failed: {}\", std::io::Error::last_os_error());\n        }\n\n        // Reap the child. SIGKILL is immediate, but `wait` is the only\n        // way to release the zombie + confirm the process is gone\n        // before we touch the WAL file from the parent.\n        wait_with_budget(&mut child, VICTIM_REAP_BUDGET, trial);\n\n        let last_commit_micros = read_last_commit_micros(&db_path);\n        let integrity = run_integrity_check(&db_path);\n        let lost_commit_ms = last_commit_micros.map(|last| {\n            // `kill_micros >= last` holds by construction (last is read\n            // from a committed row, kill_micros samples after spawn).\n            // Saturating sub guards against clock jumps under load.\n            kill_micros.saturating_sub(last) / 1_000\n        });\n        outcomes.push(TrialOutcome { integrity, lost_commit_ms });\n    }\n    outcomes\n}\n\nfn trial_sleep_ms(trial: usize) -> u64 {\n    // Deterministic linear-congruential sequence keyed off the trial\n    // index; trials remain reproducible across runs while still\n    // sweeping the kill point across the commit cycle.\n    let mixed = (trial as u64)\n        .wrapping_mul(6_364_136_223_846_793_005)\n        .wrapping_add(1_442_695_040_888_963_407);\n    let range = PWR_MAX_KILL_MS - PWR_MIN_KILL_MS;\n    PWR_MIN_KILL_MS + (mixed % range)\n}\n\nfn wait_with_budget(child: &mut std::process::Child, budget: Duration, trial: usize) {\n    let started = Instant::now();\n    loop {\n        match child.try_wait() {\n            Ok(Some(_)) => return,\n            Ok(None) => {\n                if started.elapsed() > budget {\n                    panic!(\"trial {trial}: victim did not exit within {:?} after SIGKILL\", budget);\n                }\n                std::thread::sleep(Duration::from_millis(5));\n            }\n            Err(err) => panic!(\"trial {trial}: wait failed: {err}\"),\n        }\n    }\n}\n\nfn read_last_commit_micros(db_path: &std::path::Path) -> Option<u128> {\n    // Read via the engine to confirm the engine itself can recover the\n    // killed database; raw rusqlite on a half-recovered DB might paper\n    // over an open-path defect.\n    let opened = Engine::open(db_path).expect(\"post-kill engine open\");\n    let path = opened.engine.path().to_path_buf();\n    opened.engine.close().expect(\"post-kill close\");\n    drop(opened);\n\n    let conn = rusqlite::Connection::open(&path).expect(\"post-kill rusqlite open\");\n    // Bodies are decimal microsecond timestamps; ordering by CAST keeps\n    // semantics correct if the column is TEXT-affinity.\n    let max: Option<String> = conn\n        .query_row(\n            \"SELECT body FROM canonical_nodes\n              WHERE kind = 'doc'\n              ORDER BY CAST(body AS INTEGER) DESC LIMIT 1\",\n            [],\n            |row| row.get(0),\n        )\n        .ok();\n    max.and_then(|raw| raw.parse::<u128>().ok())\n}\n\nfn run_integrity_check(db_path: &std::path::Path) -> String {\n    let conn = rusqlite::Connection::open(db_path).expect(\"integrity rusqlite open\");\n    conn.query_row(\"PRAGMA integrity_check\", [], |row| row.get::<_, String>(0))\n        .unwrap_or_else(|err| format!(\"integrity_check query failed: {err}\"))\n}\n\n// ── AC-034c: OS-crash harness ───────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n#[test]\n#[ignore = \"AC-034c blocked on missing VM/sysrq fixture; see Phase 12-D \\\n            output JSON (blocker-3). Do NOT clear the #[ignore] until \\\n            the VM image lands in dev/test-plan.md.\"]\nfn ac_034c_os_crash_zero_committed_tx_loss() {\n    // Intentionally empty body. The `#[ignore]` carries the blocker so\n    // `cargo test --release --test durability_soak ac_034c` reports\n    // \"1 ignored\" — visible in CI logs, not a silent skip — without\n    // pretending to verify the AC. Substituting `kill -9` for an OS\n    // crash would be silent AC weakening (per\n    // `feedback_reliability_principles.md` no-punt rule).\n    //\n    // To unblock: land the KVM image + `echo c > /proc/sysrq-trigger`\n    // workflow per `dev/acceptance.md` § AC-034c fixture, clear the\n    // `#[ignore]`, and wire trial loop here following the AC-034a/b\n    // shape above.\n}\n","numLines":255,"startLine":1,"totalLines":255}}}
