{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01BovpZQHi1VFeBfpAGV2uEP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Cxkg5UpjjGAU8m5mRoaVXg","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"git add -A && git commit -m \"$(cat <<'EOF'\nfix(open): probe_wal_sidecar bounded 32-byte read (12-D-fix-1 #1)\n\nThe WAL header is fixed-layout in the first 32 bytes (magic +\nformat + page-size + salts + checksums); frame data starts at\noffset 32 and is irrelevant to the magic + page-size pre-check.\n`std::fs::read` of the full sidecar was forcing an unclean-shutdown\nopen path to allocate and copy the entire WAL into memory before\nSQLite touched recovery — a measurable latency + RSS regression\nthat threatened the AC-035 recovery-time budget.\n\nReplace with `File::open` + `read_exact(&mut [u8; 32])`. New test\n`probe_wal_sidecar_bounded_read` constructs a 256 MiB sparse WAL\nsidecar with valid magic + invalid page size and asserts open\ncompletes in ≤ 200 ms (was ~318 ms against the unbounded impl on\nthe dev runner).\n\nAddresses 12-D review finding 1 (high). See\n`dev/plans/runs/12-D-review-20260517T191833Z.md`.\nEOF\n)\"","description":"Commit finding 1"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":632,"cache_read_input_tokens":67832,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":632},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3dcf3508-c16d-46fb-9860-076600a60569","uuid":"28a0049a-87b9-4991-a377-c8f52f37226a"}
