{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01YK3JfXzvZzyoJt54CUKXb2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Rgzo3aTpX16W4a5mtUhvNt","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cargo fmt --manifest-path src/rust/Cargo.toml && git add -A && git commit -m \"$(cat <<'EOF'\ntest(durability): 12-D-fix-1 findings 2/3/4\n\nFinding 2 (medium): AC-034b sentinel-wait + full-N p99. Victim\nnow writes a per-trial sentinel file after its first commit\nlands; parent blocks on the sentinel before sampling the kill\ndelay and SIGKILLing. `lost_commit_ms` becomes mandatory (no\nOption/filter), p99 is computed across the full P-PWR-TRIALS=100\nset per AC-034b contract instead of a 90 %-quorum subset.\nSentinel timeout (5 s) surfaces as a harness panic so dropouts\nare loud instead of silently discarded.\n\nFinding 3 (medium): AC-035c lock-released now spawns a true\nsibling process via `Command::new(current_exe())` routed to a new\nenv-var-gated `_lock_acquire_probe_entry`. The probe attempts\n`flock(LOCK_EX | LOCK_NB)` on the `.lock` path and exits 0/1; the\nparent asserts exit 0. Existing in-process fd reacquire kept as\na sanity check.\n\nFinding 4 (low): AC-034c body replaced with `panic!()` carrying\nthe blocker text + pointer to substrate gap. Clearing `#[ignore]`\nwithout landing the KVM image fails loudly instead of green-\npassing vacuously.\n\nAddresses 12-D review findings 2/3/4. See\n`dev/plans/runs/12-D-review-20260517T191833Z.md`.\nEOF\n)\"","description":"Apply fmt and commit"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1315,"cache_read_input_tokens":80925,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1315},"output_tokens":59,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3dcf3508-c16d-46fb